<h2 id="21-flask-routes">2.1 Flask Routes</h2>
<p><strong>What they are</strong>: URL-to-function mappings that handle HTTP requests</p>
<p><strong>Basic structure</strong>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">@app.route('/path', methods=['GET', 'POST'])
def function_name():
    # Handle request
    return response
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Route decorators explained</strong>:
- <code>@app.route()</code>: Registers function with Flask
- <code>/path</code>: URL pattern (can include variables: <code>/user/&lt;int:id&gt;</code>)
- <code>methods</code>: Allowed HTTP methods (default: GET only)</p>
<p><strong>HTTP Methods used</strong>:
| Method | Purpose | Our Usage |
